.TH "alloc_pages_exact_nid" 9 "alloc_pages_exact_nid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_pages_exact_nid \- allocate an exact number of physically-contiguous pages on a node.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" alloc_pages_exact_nid
.BI "(int nid "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nid" 12
the preferred node ID where memory should be allocated
.IP "size" 12
the number of bytes to allocate
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
GFP flags for the allocation, must not contain __GFP_COMP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Like \fBalloc_pages_exact\fP, but try to allocate on node nid first before falling
back.
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to the allocated area or NULL in case of error.
